This paper deals with the problem of balancing interpretability and accuracy in machine learning models, which is a common concern in the field of machine learning. The paper proposes a technique for optimizing the distribution of data to learn from, which can be applied to any classifier. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.ST (Statistics), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Among these, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories, as they are the most closely related to the topic of machine learning.
